The samurai's values of honor and loyalty run through the entire game. You never get bored either, you switch between story, side missions, finding shrines, hot springs, haikus, bamboo stands and so on. I encourage everyone who has not played it to give it a try. With over 50 hours playtime you really get something for your money.Ghost of Tsushima. Platin Nummer .Ein wirklich sagenhaftes Spiel. Der Mix aus Story und echten geschichtlichen Hintergrunden ist super unterhaltsam. Die Werte der Samurai von Ehre und Treue ziehen sich uber das komplette Game hinweg. Langweile kommt auch nie auf, ihr wechselt zwischen Story, Nebenmissionen, Schreine finden, Heie Quellen, Haikus, Bambusstande und so weiter. Jedem der es noch nicht gespielt hat, lege ich es ans Herz es auszuprobieren. Mit uber 50std. Spielzeit bekommt ihr fur euer Geld auch echt was geboten.

Habit  Enjoy the Little Things: Life gets busy and sometimes we get so caught up in our day-to-day routines that we fail to appreciate the little things. Whether it’s a meaningful conversation, a good meal or even a breath of fresh air, happy people know how important it is to stop and savor each and every moment.Habit  Sweat it Out: When we exercise, our bodies release chemicals called endorphins. These endorphins interact with the receptors in the brain and trigger a positive feeling in the body known as a “runner’s high.” This natural high has a profound effect on mental health, relieves stress and improves memory.Habit  Carefully Select Your ‘Friend’ Group: There’s nothing worse than being around a negative person. Their negativity is contagious and soon our mood and outlook take a nosedive. Hanging around positive people has the opposite effect. Not only do they help build our confidence, but being around them is a heck of a lot more fun.Selfave00 SelfaveSegi SEGiKD

Tips Membesarkan Anak Sesuai KarakternyaSukses atau tidaknya anak dikemudian hari ditentukan oleh potensi yang dimilikimasing-masing anak. Untuk itu, sangat penting bagi orang tua untuk memahami dan membina potensi buah hati.Menggali potensi anak ini berkaitan erat dengan pemahaman Ayah dan Bunda tentangkepribadian dan karakter anak. Pertanyaannya, tahukah Ayah dan Bunda seperti apa kepribadian dan karakter anak Anda?Jika belum, berikut tipe kepribadian yang biasanya membentuk karakter anak-anak.. Kepribadian Sempurna MelankolisTipe ini biasanya terlihat dari anak-anak yang ingin semua menjadi sempurna. Ia suka mengkritik dan bila apa yang dilakukan tidak sesuai keinginan, akan sangat kecewa. Anak tipe ini juga cenderung teratur dan tepat waktu.Ayah Bunda perlu lebih peka dengan kepribadian ini, karena cenderung butuh lebih banyak dukungan. Lakukan pendekatan komunikasi dan memberikan pemahaman yang tepat.Anak-anak tipe ini biasanya sangat tidak kompetitif dan tidak peduli dengan hadiah, karena dirinya menuntut kesempurnaan yang diharapkan sendiri.. Kepribadian Sangunis PopulerTipe ini senang berkumpul, raman dan supel. Suka mencari perhatian, kasih sayang dan dukungan orang sekitar. Mereka cenderung penuh kegembiraan dan memiliki energi besar.Namun, mereka cenderung sangat sensitif, emosional, dan tidak teratur. Dukunglah anak-anak tipe ini jadi aktif lewat komunitas atau kegemarannya. Kepribadian Kuat KolerisTipe ini sangat mengejar prestasi, selalu menuntut penghargaan, dan loyalitas orang sekitar.Orang tua perlu melakukan pendekatan komunikasi, agar anak tipe ini tidak mudah tersinggung.Tipe ini lebih menghargai kejujuran, keadilan, dan logika. Untuk itu, baiknya paparkan dengan jelas tujuan, tugas dan apa yang orang tua harapkan pada anak. Koleris terkenal tegas, pekerja keras, ekstrovert, optimis, dan cenderung ambisius.So, mana tipe kepribadian dan karakter anak Anda?ESQ - Expert in Character Building

KNOW THE PRISONED BHIMA KOREGAON 12: RONA WILSONRona Wilson, the committed political prisoner’s rights activist, was arrested for belonging allegedly to the “top brass of urban Maoists”. Prior to his arrest he had been preoccupied with the research proposal for his application to a PhD programme at a university in the UK. Rona came to Delhi in 1990, where he was based, from Kolam district in Kerala to study at JNU.Rona was the founding member of the Committee for the Release of Political Prisoners. He was involved in organizing protest against the constant targeting of Muslims under various draconian laws like UAPA. He was one of the most active persons involved in the campaign for the release of SAR Geelani who was illegally arrested in the case of parliament attack along with Afzal Guru. Likewise, he had campaigned for those people who had been illegally detained by the police just because of their political activism or ideology. He has campaigned for the release of Prof GN Saibaba, Hem Mishra and others who had been arrested for speaking against operation Green Hunt. An uncompromising fighter for human rights and a sharp intellectual mind, Rona was deeply committed in challenging the overall model of development in India which involved displacement of Adivasis and Dalits from their Jal, Jungle and Zameen. On 6 June 2018, Rona was arrested on the basis of certain letters that contained "plot to assassinate the Prime Minister". Though none of the charges have been proved yet and certain malware were found from his computer signaling the letter might be false or implanted, he is locked up in at Taloja Jail in Mumbai along with his fellow prisoners.ReleasethePoet

：【Kodak 業務用 100】除了Fuji與Konica外，早年Kodak亦曾經推出過業務用菲林。Kodak的業務用菲林，貫徹品牌的暖調作風，充滿豐富濃艷的色彩，而且對比度高，適合各種人像與風景拍攝。業務用亦意味着這是一般性的消費性菲林，意思是它的影像未能如電影菲林般展現細緻、均衡的成色，但無論在日光下拍攝或是加上閃光，這款菲林依然能呈現生動的色彩，充分滿足不同的拍攝需求。註：Kodak業務用菲林為絕版過期菲林，這一批過期年份為13年5月。--售價：$55-面交：港鐵沿線郵寄：順豐到付/本地平郵

El conocer y el aprender son cualidades que definen al ser humano pero, he de anadir una mas profunda. Hay una cualidad como intencionalidad de ser, por la que toda nuestra naturaleza parece que apetece existir. Se da como un don y asi hay una intencionalidad profunda, la mas basica, en el hombre que es el pensar. Ansia ser, existir, dar vida, hacer existir. Y todo ello se constituye en el amar, en la ayuda a los demas, en la creatividad y la productividad. Y si se va en contra de estas aspiraciones tan fundamentales del hombre, el individuo y la sociedad se enferman.Reflexionar sobre lo humano remite a la necesidad de saber quienes somos, esta constante busqueda que reafirma que nuestra vida interior es lo que pensamos. La manera en la que pensamos determina como vivimos y quienes somos. Por ello es importante meditar sobre lo que estamos pensando y decidimos hacer. “Porque cual es su pensamiento en su corazn, tal es l" (Proverbios 23 : 7)moodthehub_photography_vision_toplifeabsolute_photography_addictedsouls_globe_drama_artstyle_greatshotsamateurs__users_planetpocket_

Meet Jacob Sherry, AIA | LEED AP BD+C, a licensed Architect working with 510 Architects in Richmond, VA. Jake grew up in Laurel, Maryland and ventured south in 2008 to study at Virginia Tech. There he received a Bachelor of Architecture and a minor in Music for percussion in 2013, which led him to accept a full-time job in RVA. Living and working in Richmond for the past seven years has matured his love for  within a cultural and vibrant community. Jake is interested in many aspects of  but his passion stems from the expression of constructability + materiality in the built environment, more specifically applied to urban infill + adaptive reuse projects. He channels these interests in his work with 510 as well as volunteering for the RVA YAF committee where he champions the organization of hardhat tours and various young professional outings to promote out-of-office learning experiences to Richmond’s emerging professionals. Outside of , Jake loves golfing, jiu jitsu, sports, gardening, live music, and frequenting all of the breweries in the greater Richmond area.We are happy to have  as part of our team and we can’t wait to see what this year has in store for him! 我家附近的頂好裝潢更新服務變得超好 食材也超新鮮我好喜歡喔哈哈哈昨天遇到的   人很好我們四點半因為太餓受不了就去吃滷味 他點了很多夾三分之一給我雖然是很微不足道的事情，但這一瞬間我真心覺得「最美的的是人心」上上禮拜和一位從日本工作回來的   聊天在離開的時候她對我說「今天很高興認識你」那句話我非常有印象的留在腦海我覺得這是一句很令人開心的話所以我決定每一次也都必須跟其他說這句話中山tomods總是有很多觀光客 以致於我也有機會接受日本或歐美的旅客詢問商品當他們知道我並非店員卻願意替他們解答時，總會頻頻向我說 我覺得非常滿足無論今天是外國人或是台灣人如果我能用自己的小小知識和你交流跟幫助到你那我覺得我今天過得很有意義昨晚吃飯的時候聽到餐廳其他客人大叫有聖誕老公公我也拿著手機衝出去 看起來是車聚看到這個畫面，不知道為什麼我滿開心的，覺得很可愛也覺得世界很美好送小肌肉回家後，隨手一招搭乘   回家司機送我一包暖暖包，還和我分享很多保健小知識我覺得非常幸運，能夠遇到這位司機偶爾我覺得很神奇，自己好像很容易被搭話有一兩次對方都直接跟我說「因為感覺跟你有緣份」「因為你散發一種很好的氣質」這種話好像真的頗搭訕的但我覺得我聽得出來你是否真心誠意還是有目地的亂槍打鳥最近星期日都會拋下最愛的慾望城市 跟媽媽去散步運動雖然很捨不得 可是抽時間跟家人相處真的非常棒想做的事情有很多，學習日文／英文、環遊世界、努力賺錢買房子……etc雖然一直在工作，沒有多餘的時間，但我也在思考自己是不是不夠有效擅用時間是否工作沒效率無法正常下班，無法好好利用空檔睡不飽太累真的會影響思考和腦袋的運作但我覺得這樣的事情在我身上是不允許發生因為副業而影響正職是粉墨導致或許會計部不是那麼討喜，給人家的刻板印象就是不知變通又機車但我依舊慶幸進入會計部因為他們其實很可愛心腸也很好非常體諒我是腦殘 也很願意教導及分享我的國中高中一直是女校但國小就接觸同性戀這件事情雖然我是乖乖牌（？）但意外我都會跟壞學生混在一起只是我都是裡面的俗辣 無法同進同退（汗）我的父母也是很傳統的人雖然因應世代交替，對我的教育能夠開放到這樣的程度大概也是極限了對於接受跟不接受同性戀的議題我們都不能逼對方認同或不認同我一直覺得大家都說得很好聽，好朋友或家人要說實話但台灣人在聽實話的接受度根本不高好像無所謂但其實超級有所謂的放心裡所以我不太喜歡跟人家說實話，即時姐妹「尊重」真的很重要我也很努力的實踐這個行為我要來煎牛排了

在是個方便的交通工具，舉個手就有，打電話或app叫車也是方便，有捷運、公車，都營業到半夜，如果都沒有時還有Ubike，總之不可能回不了家。三年前我騎著自行車環島，我以為到處都很方便，不會沒地方住、不會買不到水、不會沒有7-11、不會沒有人，我帶著星巴克、摩斯儲值卡，想說騎累了就吃一頓喝一杯，但一路上我只在高雄用過一次，除了天氣熱以外，就是水喝完，如果錯過補給站，就要再騎個兩三個小時才有下一個補給，如果騎太晚根本沒有路燈，騎到田中間燈又沒電，你就可能一不小心摔進田裡，那次的環島我感受到許多南北的差異，但也因此愛上除了的地方。阿母說要來找我順便旅遊，要我不用管他，他可以自理，但我說了交通不便喔！她回答我她可以坐，我告訴她路上沒有，她生氣說是我不想讓她來找我的理由還真是冤枉。朋友們更是天真的說，那打啊！！我說沒有～～更有人提議，那打Uber啊？！我連Uber eats都沒得叫了就是不一樣 人 女婿人俗eats

第一次做的介面設計作品本業是平面設計，剛好在去年的求職經驗裡誤打誤撞接觸到介面設計，如果要說契機，反而比較像因為長久以來接觸平面設計的經驗，讓我發現介面設計的方法論可以有系統的解決自己的弱點。大約半年一直在學習，不過還沒用到SKETCH，就連這個side project也是以PHOTOSHOP土法煉鋼做出來的。現在回頭看，不論是guideline或以自己角度來看的易用性、流暢度，完全不及格 品牌也沒做好，我不懂我為什麼當初想做這樣而且是在沒做使用者研究的情況下，把自己對taxi app的想法做出來，有夠北蘭，我半年前竟然敢拿這個爛東西去丟面試，我真的是遇到菩薩 總之今天的感覺是步上某個軌道，作品集也以非常緩慢的速度進行中。

老闆切了一瓣柳丁給小男孩說：你幫我試試甜不甜。簡單的一件事道盡了人與人之間的親密感與信任感，不管是家人之間、夫妻間、情侶間或朋友間。今天是我人生第一次躺在手術檯上，腦中出現各種沒有連結的畫面。韓劇Doctors的手術場景而我是飾演其中的個案；想像著我閉上眼睛就能到達所謂天使會去的地方；也閃過媽媽躺在病床上的無助和害怕，我小心翼翼的拭淚擔心護士覺得我太膽小因為我也只是小小的指甲切除手術。然後要拭淚了才發現我全身僵硬腳還沒打麻醉藥手已經麻了。醫生拿了兩個針頭說要幫我粗的換細的，我問說有什麼差別嗎然後突然意識到我可能到死前都會這麽愚蠢。對，開這刀一點都不痛；而我也不是因為怕痛流淚。還好最後搭上的是講話溫柔又年輕的運將的如果是咀檳榔又粗理粗氣的我一定爆哭。弱到爆的台版Doctors

週五夜晚的微醺光影，總讓我們想起一些過往。.有關的發起，這整件事的開始，其實只是一個突發奇想，加上愛作夢的衝動，又天生「」（註一）的驅力，讓我們踏上這整個冒險的旅程。.大概在去年這個時候，我們草創了，也在11月份成功的在橋頭老房子這，開始介紹丹麥老件家具給來參觀的朋友。不得不說，這對非藝術相關專長的我們來說，確是個不小的挑戰。.在這三百多天的日子裡，我們除了對於自己的想法更為清晰外，更加認識了不少志同道合的好朋友，包含一直支持我們的藝術創作者，以及全力配合我們的工班師傅們。.「在這裡，我要好好的謝謝他們， 少了你們，我們可能還只是在白日夢， 還只是香腸攤那青澀的面孔。」.最近我們啟動了一個新的計畫，心中只有一個簡單的期望，就是不要辜負這些支持我們的朋友，以及自己對屋物的期待與。我想我們可以，也必須可以！.常常有人問，屋物這名字的由來。其實只是源自我們對丹麥設計的熱愛，而以丹麥首都哥本哈根地理位置（北緯55度41分），節錄55而發展為「屋物」。這也符合我們對品牌價值的期待：「推廣屋裡好物，分享藝文生活的美好。」介紹我們心目中美好的事物，讓到來的朋友能有所感受，並與自己的生活產生共鳴。.這樣就讓我們很滿足了。..剩下的，就讓我們多一點，也讓期待，能逐步實現。..（註一）《！》，作者：石田裕輔。..

That's relativity.”— Albert Einstein.愛因斯坦曾經說過：「當你把手放在熱鍋上一分鐘，感覺像一小時；但坐在美女身旁一小時，覺得只過了一分鐘。」這種在不使用任何計時工具的情況下，對客觀現象的延續性和順序性的感知，有個專有名詞稱為「時間知覺」(Time Perception)，白話一點就是我們常講的時間感。而有趣的是，通常人們處於正面情緒(positive emotion)的狀態時，對時間的主觀感知會加快，也影響對事物的看法。.Sackett等人在2010年於Psychological Science期刊發表的研究指出，當實驗者讓參與者經歷愉悅（相對於不愉悅）的情境後，接著調查參與者任務經歷的時間感受，結果發現感覺愉悅的組別，時間知覺較快。更有趣的是，在隨後的研究中發現，當人們知覺時間過得比較快時，煩人的噪音變得沒那麼厭惡，好聽的歌曲也覺得更加好聽了。.這就好像，心情好看什麼都好的道理。所以當我們處於正面情緒，相信對身邊的人或者自己，都能有一定程度的正面影響。.我們致力於分享藝文生活的美好，也相信舒適的生活環境能帶來許多好處，除了紓解一天辛勤的疲憊外，也促使我們往正面的思考方向，調節生活瑣事的煩躁，提昇美好事物的效果，讓我們有更好的生活品質。.分享藝文生活的美好，屋物生活知識，我們下次見。.參考文獻：Sackett, A. M., Meyvis, T., Nelson, L. D., Converse, B. A., & Sackett, A. L. (2010). You’re having fun when time flies: The hedonic consequences of subjective time progression. 0265G通訊時代即將來臨，相較於現行的4G LTE ，5G有「高速」、「低延遲」、「廣連結」等特性。物理上，想實現「高功率傳輸」的，有個重要的叫做「」。具有高頻、抗輻射、耐高壓電等物理特性，在高功率傳輸上，有其不可替代的物理性質優勢，因此可說是5G通訊元件的關鍵材料！除了應用於商用無線通訊、光通訊，也應用於先進的國防、航空及衛星用途。台灣的晶圓代工能力是世界一流的，本週要介紹的個股，是產業的龍頭公司——！，成立於1999年，全名「股份有限公司」，是全球首座以六英吋晶圓生產「微波積體電路」的專業晶圓代工公司，於2010年起成為全球最大晶圓代工廠商。關於，以下是人可關注的點：1產業成長性：元件是無線通訊產業的關鍵零組件，隨著5G世代的開啟，元件的用量比起以前將有增無減。除了5G外，3D感測、光通訊應用的崛起，也帶動元件的需求，而此類的製程往往須具備特殊的設備與製作流程，亦為的發展利基之一。2規模與市佔率：近年持續提升晶圓的產能。2018年底，月產能為32,000片。2019年底，月產能達到36,000片。預計2020年第2季開始，月產能可達41,000片。此外，目前晶圓代工巿場，的市佔率超過七成。（資訊來源：2019年11月業績發表會）3製程：有自主研發新產品之能力。目前在無線寬頻通訊的微波高領域，提供「異質接面雙極性電晶體」和「應變式異質接面高遷移率電晶體」，兩者均為最尖端的製程。為特殊材料，通常門檻較高的產業，較不易出現新的競爭者。-（3105）：全球最大晶圓代工廠.2020/04/14收盤價：273元（一張1000股=273,000元）近一年股價變化：上漲60元，漲幅+28.2%。2019年股利：每股配發現金5元，年均殖利率約2.15%。（若在2019/04/15買進一張，至今可賺到價差60,000元，並領到現金股利5,000元）.2020年股利：預計配發現金7元，現價殖利率約2.56%。.小筆記：台灣有三大代工廠：（3105）、環宇-KY（4991）、宏捷科（8086）。-所有內容僅供參考，無任何買賣建議martket      4G 5G 5G基地台 5G概念股

Here’s something my father calls something thoroughly unrelated but, evidently, it’s commonly -in real life- referred to as “moo palo”. Make and peel some medium-boiled eggs and set aside. Sear some fatty pork shoulder (I cut it into 5 or 6 thick, palm-sized pieces) and add enough chicken or pork stock( or broth) to cover the pork. Set to low and add a couple tbsp of 5-spice powder, a couple tbsp of sweet soy sauce, and maybe 10 full star anise clusters. Eating this stew when I was growing up these vibrant pods just floated around and ended up being chewed up. I’m an adult now, dammit. I put my star anise in a big tea ball so I can remove them all in one go. (Somehow that sentence makes me seem less adult.) Cover this and let it simmer on low for usually 4 hrs but start checking on it around 3 to see how pull aparty the pork is. If it’s easily pull aparty taste the broth. Here you’ll want to add some fish sauce, some golden mountain thai soy sauce, and maybe some hoisin sauce or brown sugar. Once it’s to your perception of balanced and flavorful add the peeled eggs from before and let it simmer maybe another 20 minutes. In the meantime slice your cucumber, green onion, cilantro, and lime and make some rice or noodles. Remove the eggs and let them cool before slicing; I use a cheese slicer. Serve sort of as seen here. That’s some prik nam pla on the side with chopped cilantro stems, by the way.    pork

If you love Lor Mee, hesitate no more... Just do it!! Yellow noodles are soaked in a dark gooey sauce topped with yummy braised meat, egg and crispy fish fillets! [Method]1 Add 6 cups of water into a deep pot. Add in the dark soya sauce, rock sugar, garlic and ginger. Add in the 5-spice powder and bring to boil.2 Next, put the pork belly into the boiling sauce and simmer on low/medium fire for about 40 minutes. Turn the meat once or twice and cover the pot partially. After 40 minutes, add in the hard-boiled eggs and simmer for another 20 minutes. Remove pork belly and eggs and set aside. Remove ginger slices and reserve the garlic cloves.3 Add in the black vinegar and salt. Adjust according to taste. Slowly add the beaten eggs to the braising liquid while stirring in a circular motion. 4 Next add the cornstarch solution to the braising liquid slowly and let it boil on low heat. the braising liquid will thicken into luscious gravy.5Deep fry the fish cake and the tempura fish fillet according to the instructions on the packet. Slice the fish cake thinly and the fish fillet into 2 cm slices.6 Blanched the yellow noodles or wholegrain noodles for 2 minutes in boiling water. Drain and divide into the 5 bowls with 2 pieces of lettuce in it. Add in the reserved garlic cloves.7 Slicethe pork belly thinly into 1 cm strips. Divide equally or unequally and on top of the noodles. Place one whole braised egg on each bowl of noodle and halve it. Then divide the fried fish fillet and fish cake equally on top of each bowl.8 Next, place the 5 bowls of Lor Mee on the dining table. Transfer the whole pot of gravy from the stove-top to the dining table. Caution! It"s Hot!! Ladel the gravy generously on each bowl of noodles and watch everyone drool!!! Sprinkle some fried onions before serving.* Note: You can also add deep fried-till-crispy sliced ikan kurau salted fish,wanton & ngoh hiang (meat roll)... super delicious!!---

Duck confit| 5 Spice pak Choi| Indian  sauce| Ruharb & green apple sauce| Potato fondant| Purple carrotDuck will be on far more menus in France than those in North America or the UK. The method of raising ducks and geese for their meat and fattened liver was brought to France by the Romans. The Romans also brought many other farming methods including planting fruit trees such as the apricot, cherry, plum, and peach among many others. The Romans also brought their knowledge for farm-raising snails. In France, the Romans did more than just build their usual boring straight roads, amphitheaters, baths, and temples etc. They brought ducks, geese, fruit trees, snails and more.Traditionally Duck confit served with plum sauce.A duck confitis made by cooking the meat in its own fat and juices. After cooking the duck will be preserved under a layer of its own natural fat in a glass or glazed pottery container. A confit would not have been invented today; everyone has refrigerators. However, the unique taste that a confit creates keeps the recipe popular. When the confit is served the fat will be removed.N.B.: In French, a prune means a plum and a prune is a pruneau, pronounced prune-oh.               porn stagram  eeee e     respect

Some days I wish we had a grill...5 Spice Chicken Skewers INGREDIENTS 2 lb boneless chicken tenders 2 Tbsp granulated erythritol sweetener** (honey for Paleo) 2 Tbsp five spice powder 1 Tbsp unsweetened rice wine vinegar 1 Tbsp avocado oil (or other light oil with a high smoke point) 1 tsp sesame oil 1 Tbsp gluten free soy sauce, fish sauce, or coconut aminos** 1/2 tsp cayenne pepper (optional) 1 cup red bell pepper pieces for skewers optional  wedges and fresh cilantro to garnish 12 skewersINSTRUCTIONS1) Slice the chicken thinly on the diagonal into pieces about 2 inches long.2) Combine the sweetener, 5 spice powder, rice vinegar, avocado oil, sesame oil, soy sauce (or fish sauce or coconut aminos) and cayenne pepper (if using) in a medium bowl and stir.3) Taste for seasoning and adjust sweetness or saltiness to your preference BEFORE adding the chicken.4) Add the chicken pieces and stir well to coat.5) Marinate the chicken for at least 1 hour and up to 24 hours.6) Preheat the grill.7) Thread the chicken and red bell pepper pieces (or other veggies) onto the skewers. Grill for 2 -3 minutes per side or until the chicken is cooked through.9) Garnish with  wedges and fresh cilantro if desired.Enjoy!’

This beautiful looking pressure cooker cooked ' paanch phoron' Bengali  style sabzi by my mom is THE BOMB!!  Its one of those quick cooking recipies & always works its magic on me!! We love cooking it in a pressure cooker(my fav Indian kitchen utensil) as it really helps blend in the flavours & make a yummy little gravy & ofcourse because a pressure cooker cooks everything faster & saves time & gas & is basically an Indian kitchens life!!! Mom used  but you could use sweet potato,potato,yam,taro,karela or mixed veggies or meats etc. I loveee eating it with ghee rice or garam garam chapatti! Or paired with a mutton curry as a side!!! YUMMMPanch phoron is a whole spice blend, originating from the Eastern India, mainly in the Bengal and Northeast India region and used especially in the cuisine of West Bengal, Northeastern India, Nepal and Bangladesh. The name literally means "five spices" used for tempering daals,vegetables,chutneys & pickles.Main ingredients:Methi(Fenugreek seeds),Kalongi(Nigella seeds), Jeera(Cumin seeds),Rye(Black mustard seeds) and Saunf(Fennel seeds)Recipe comming sooon!!!!             indian

I always make some kind of bread when we have soup for dinner. Just to make it a bit more substantial. I wanted to try a new bread recipe so I was really happy to come across this recipe. The dough does not contain any yeast so it doesn’t take that much time to make. The filling is simple too as it consist of only chickpeas, some spices and spring onions. The sesame seeds where a complete disaster though . About 80% of the sesame seeds burned in the pan/oil when frying them. The 5-spice and the soy sauce in this recipe give this bread a delicious Asian flavour. The kids absolutely loved it and we will be making them again soon. Sometimes our “what if’s” are full of fear, fortune telling, conclusion jumping and a giant bucket full of anticipatory anxiety. We consider all of the worst case scenarios, try to control the uncontrollable and move through life as though we are certain of what’s to come. We convince ourselves that we KNOW how the story unfolds and we create a narrative that supports our racing thoughts and keeps our dysregulated behavior in overdrive. In our quest to self-protect, the illusion of certainty pours into our open wounds and anesthetizes our pain. It feels good and powerful at first but it is impossible to sustain. We forget how often we are wrong. We forget how often other people are wrong. In a world full of “experts” it is easy to be influenced and numbed by the constant chatter of predictions, opinions, recommendations and advice giving. There is so much talking. So, so, so much talking. “What if” can be a question of fear or a declaration of possibility. What if you already have the answers you are seeking? What if it’s okay to be wrong, to fail, to feel, to hurt, to lose, to succeed, to go first, to be wrong or to not fix? What if it’s okay to accept yourself exactly as you are over and over again without changing a thing? What if it’s okay to not know. What if it’s okay to disagree and still be kind? What if it’s okay to let people live their own lives? What if this place you are in is leading you to the exact place you are going? What if you said no? What if you said yes? What if you tuned everyone else out and tuned into yourself? What if you felt the fear and did it anyway? What if!!!! What if!!! What if!!!
The only way you’ll see results is if you stay consistent so don’t give up!

Al llegar, recorrimos el centro de Puerto Baquerizo Moreno y alguna de sus playas, como Playa Mann y Playa Punta Carola. Terminamos la tarde en la zona del mirador del Cerro Tijeretas. Al da siguiente, nos embarcamos nuevamente para hacer una excelente snorkel en la zona de la Roca Len Dormido o Kicker Rock. Terminando nuestro viaje volvimos a Santa Cruz para disfrutar de un festival de danzas local y luego comenzar nuestro retorno a Uruguay. We found a very random selection on  tonight for a place called Japanese Rice Bowl Association. I've never heard of the place before and when I tried googling it the only results are for food delivery apps. The food choices sounded pretty good so we thought we'd give it a shot..We ordered two of their bowls, Japanese Pork Cutlet Curry and the Japanese Curry Don. We also got two sides, Chicken Karaage and Potato Croquettes. Delivery was free for over $30 and Skip had a coupon offer for $7 off. Total with tip and tax came to $32. For anyone who uses a delivery service, this is actually a pretty decent price for the amount of food we ordered..We didn't want to get our hopes up on taste so we went in with no expectations. The food was delivered quicker than usual despite the distance and everything was still hot and crispy when I opened the containers. To our surprise everything was actually quite good! When was this place added and how come I didn't order from here earlier? Brown gives it two paws up!

What used to be a near weekly event in my pre-pandemic life has become less frequent lately, as these gatherings have been replaced with socially distanced picnics with takeout, which are great as well.. is one of my favourite spots in Yaletown for happy hour. They have a large happy hour menu of seafood-based appies, plus a relatively extensive selection of discounted drinks. We ordered nearly the entire food menu, including mussels ($11.25), garlic toast ($3.50), Parmesan fries ($6.75), grilled oysters ($3.50 each), halibut poppers ($7.75), chicken wings ($7.75), tuna poke ($9.25), and the lobster & shrimp rolls ($5 each). All the food items were fantastic, with my favourite dishes being the mussels, halibut poppers, and the lobster & shrimp rolls. The patio is perfect for a summer day and tables are separated with plexiglass..Wild Tale is located in Yaletown  1079 Mainland St, Vancouver. All day happy hour on Sundays and Mondays. Happy hour from 3 to 6pm and 9pm until close all other days.

The problem I have when it comes to eating vegan meals during the weekdays is the lack of flavor and I don’t like to cook. The best part is all the meals come cooked upon delivery in a chilled bag! Just reheat and eat! Pictured are the following dishes.- Shepard’s pie- Spaghetti and Meatballs- Chicken tikka masala- Thai Beef SaladMy favorite was the Chicken tikka masala and the Thai Beef Salad.The chicken I could tell was not chicken but the sauce surprised me. They used a lot of spices along with coconut milk making it creamy. The spiciness was on the medium side and definitely packed flavor! The Thai beef salad had a delicious peanut based sauce and the texture of the beef was very similar to ground beef. The mixture of sauce, herbs, and meat texture made me forget it was plant based! is offering 10% your order using coupon code PlantXYVRThanks again  for the meals!

COOKIES  OR BROOKIES?! WE’LL TAKE BOTH Paula Bakes...We think we have a cookie addiction. Finally tried out Paula’s delicious cookies . She’s a home baker in Vancouver that bakes a variety of baked goods but some of her signatures items are her Chocolate Chip Cookies & Brookies!.CHOCOLATE CHIP COOKIEThese were so thin and chewy. We really liked how it was just very simple in ingredients but a classic. We enjoyed them! So much better than supermarket cookies. You taste more of the chocolate chips & butter flavour. It’s not too sweet either so it was perfect..BROOKIEIt was our first time trying this kinda cookie and as brownie fans we loved them. If you haven’t tried a brookie you have got to check them out! So good, it’s literally a brownie in cookie form. Her cookies are quite delicate and super soft and chewy. It had a rich chocolate fudge taste and it was just delicious ..TLDR; If you’re craving cookies that are simple and classy her cookies are for you! Her BROOKIES are so unique. She also makes other beautiful baked goods and unique creations so check her out and DM to order !.Thank you  for the delicious cookies! ..- yvr

A huge part of being able to achieve big goals in life is to be able to accept and handle rejections well. No matter who we are, beautiful or ugly, tall or short, skinny or fat, rich or poor, we are all human. At some point in life, we will all experience rejection. If you allow rejections to intimidate you, then you won’t get very far in life. Instead, don’t take rejections personal. Understand that at the end of the day, everybody has their own opinions and preferences. Once you understand and accept this fact, rejections won’t bother you. Once rejections has no effect on your mood and self esteem, you’ll have the courage to continue in striving for success.Photographer:

|  :    " "In a world locked down, our social life has drastically changed over the past half-year. Especially on how we interact with our colleagues, many of us heavily rely on video conferencing. This has led to the growth of a new psychological phenomenon: ZOOM FATIGUE.Named in reference to the popular video conferencing platform Zoom, “Zoom Fatigue” is characterized by physical and emotional exhaustion from the overuse of video conferencing applications such as Skype, Google Meet and Zoom itself. Anxiety about having to participate in video chats and one’s performance during such chats is also common.Here are five strategies for mitigating Zoom Fatigue:1 Save video chatting for when absolutely necessary. Meet in person with those in your bubble. Don’t use video chat for something for which you would have just picked up the phone prior to self-isolation. Try group texting and having fun with emojis2 Suggest going audio-only sometimes or having only the person speaking turn on their video3 Don’t be afraid to ask for breaks during long session4 Set up different spaces for your work and social video chatting. Have where you video chat with friends and family be somewhere casual where you feel comfortable and relaxed5 Try digital detoxing other parts of your life to balance out the extra screen time spent video chattingVideo conferencing becomes the new norm now. We can adapt to a 'new normal' very quickly it turns out. Sometimes it could be frustrating and fatigue, but when it works, it can lead to genuine connection.Humans are the most adaptive species, we have the ability to evolve, which allows us to find our mental footing.

Behind the scenes photos from the set of the  serial Power of the Daleks I came across these clippings in a DWM and was really impressed with the quality. For the standards of Dr Who photos from that time these are really sharp and unlike the show, in colour. I was especially drawn to the close up picture of the  which looked as though the photo had been taken today. Finds like this are really exciting as, obviously Power of the Daleks no longer exists save for a few short clips, some of which are quite low quality as they were filmed off of a TV screen. And yet, despite the elusive story we have things like this that give us a vivid glimpse into the past and the production of this long lost story from over half a century ago..In the second individual photo you'll notice cardboard cutouts of s in the background. Obviously these were a budget saving measure to increase the  numbers. It's pretty funny to see but I admire what they were going for. And to be fair, it is doubtful that people watching on tiny black & white TV screens from the  would have quickly picked up on the tricky ruse...  classic  classic  s thes               19  vintage movies design

Genesis Begins Again (Hardcover)Author: Alicia D. Williams**RESTOCK ALERT****Grade Level (4 - 8) Price: $17.99This deeply sensitive and powerful debut novel tells the story of a thirteen-year-old who must overcome internalized racism and a verbally abusive family to finally learn to love herself.There are ninety-six things Genesis hates about herself. She knows the exact number because she keeps a list. Like : Because her skin is so dark, people call her charcoal and eggplant—even her own family. And : Because her family is always being put out of their house, belongings laid out on the sidewalk for the world to see. When your dad is a gambling addict and loses the rent money every month, eviction is a regular occurrence.What’s not so regular is that this time they all don’t have a place to crash, so Genesis and her mom have to stay with her grandma. It’s not that Genesis doesn’t like her grandma, but she and Mom always fight—Grandma haranguing Mom to leave Dad, that she should have gone back to school, that if she’d married a lighter skinned man none of this would be happening, and on and on and on. But things aren’t all bad. Genesis actually likes her new school; she’s made a couple friends, her choir teacher says she has real talent, and she even encourages Genesis to join the talent show.But how can Genesis believe anything her teacher says when her dad tells her the exact opposite? How can she stand up in front of all those people with her dark, dark skin knowing even her own family thinks lesser of her because of it? Why, why, why won’t the lemon or yogurt or fancy creams lighten her skin like they’re supposed to? And when Genesis reaches  on the list of things she hates about herself, will she continue on, or can she find the strength to begin again?

This program will help pay for portions of unpaid rent for the months of April, May, June, July, and August 2020. The application period is Monday, August 31 through Sunday, September 6, 2020, from 8 a.m. to 10 p.m. daily.The funds provided are not a loan and does not have to be repaid.Individuals may be eligible if they meet the following requirements: They are a Broward County resident; They or someone in their household experienced a documented loss or reduction in income related to COVID-19; Due to the loss of income related to COVID-19, they were unable to pay their rent; and Their landlord agrees to participateRead more at Davie-fl.gov

I made a choice a little over a month ago to get serious about my health so I joined a challenge group..This was around the same time that the government started talking about sending teachers back into the building with students.  I realized then that I needed to have options in my life. Sure, I chose to become a teacher and I could have chosen any profession, but I didn’t want to be forced to go back to a brick and mortar school during a pandemic. At the end of the day though, I still have bills to pay..I found out that my fitness journey had an opportunity for me to build a business while helping people start their own fitness journeys right along side me.  I didn’t know it then, but I have been waiting for this opportunity!  I decided to go all in and I am determined to be successful in every aspect of it! It has been a little over a month and the future is so bright. .I am continuing to work hard everyday to meet the needs of my students as a teacher, but also building the foundation and framework for the life I want to live. I don’t know what tomorrow will bring, but I do know that I am happy to be on this path today and I want to bring others along for this glorious ride!- - .If you are looking for options in your life, we should connect, I want to share this opportunity that was shared with me. Mamas,”Wear the damn bathing suit so you don’t miss out on time with your family. Rather than sit on the side of the pool fully-clothed worrying about the size of your thighs, put on your bathing suit and play Marco Polo in the pool with your kids. Teach your littles how to do cannonballs. Make memories with your family rather than sit on the sidelines and watch memories being made around you.The truth is, your kids won’t remember your stretch marks, baby weight or the c-section shelf. Your kids will remember the afternoon you spent building the largest sandcastle they have ever seen or those morning swims at the neighborhood pool.Maybe if all of us moms got out this summer and wore our damn bathing suits, it would help encourage other moms to get out there and do the same.We only get so many summers with our kids, let’s not waste them worrying about how we look—instead, let’s just wear the damn bathing suit.”  Today was a first and quite the milestone for Lovey & mama.

There is no hard and fast rule to this , PUT in work and you will see results . Are u natural or surgery? I AM ALL NATURAL .. I have been working out for a long long time ... Besides there  is no doctor in the world who will give you a toned sexy thigh if you don’t put in  work  . They would also tell you to work out . Ma voi ve li portate i cani in vacanza?I nostri vengono con noi quasi (quasi perch evitiamo stress inutili) ovunque.E ogni volta che partiamo per un nuovo viaggio, affrontiamo un nuovo percorso o viviamo nuove esperienze, piazzano sta faccia felice che  una goduria da vedere.Sanno comunicare cos bene la loro felicit che vale tutta l'immensa "rottura di palle" di portarsi il proprio cane appresso."Rottura di palle" perch  un casino gestire i pelosi, prendersi cura di loro e ragionare su spostamenti idonei anche alle loro esigenze."Rottura di palle" perch se vuoi essere un buon padrone devi impegnarti. Devi essere in grado di prenderti delle responsabilit, di saperti organizzare e rendere dignitosa l'esistenza dei tuoi cani.Rispettando le esigenze e necessit di questi cuori pulsanti che dipendono da te.Esempio?Io sono talmente abituata a fare camminate con almeno un cane al mio fianco da pi di 9 anni che a camminare da sola mi sento persa (e anche un po' scema) e perdo lo scopo della mia passeggiata.Ormai sono totalmente dipendente dalla "rottura di palle" che i miei cani mi provocano.E non potrei essere, anzi potremmo perch  sta messo uguale, pi felici di vivere insieme all'immensa "rottura di palle" che noi chiamiamo Seta&Sugar 26.8 Giornata Internazionale del Cane

Bun Bun hasn't felt well today. She didn't want any treats and wasn't moving much and couldn't get into a comfortable position and she didn't eat all day. The last time she ate was this morning and I tried to get her to drink some pineapple juice which she refused, and she hadn't gone to the bathroom all day. I was worried all day and we were almost ready to take her to the emergency room. But I was finally able to get some pineapple juice down and then took here outside to see if she would move around a little since she loves being outside. It did get her moving a little which was positive to see and then she ate some plantain leaves in the yard. I let her rest for an hour and she finally went to the bathroom. She's been improving and acting more like herself which is a great relief. Plantain leaf is known to help digestion upsets, I think it's so neat to see how nature heals..........               style             flop

We end up getting taken advantage of by those who don’t deserve our time, emotional labor, or love, and bend over backwards trying to impress people that WE ARE TOO GOOD FOR. Imagine what we could do if we trashed the norms, focused all that energy on ourselves, and step into our power. Imagine if we supported each other instead of settling and fighting for crumbs.
